{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4404399625","title":"Senior People & Culture Manager - Paris & Casablanca","company":"Norton Rose Fulbright","location":"Global","remote":false,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://nrf.wd3.myworkdayjobs.com/External/job/Paris-France/Senior-People---Culture-Manager---Paris---Casablanca_R-3882?Source=APPLICANT_SOURCE-Linkedin","description":"Practice Group / Department:\n\nPeople & Culture Business Partnering - Europe\n\nJob Description\n\nWe're Norton Rose Fulbright - a global law firm with over 50 offices and 7,000 employees worldwide. We provide the world’s preeminent corporations and financial institutions with a full business law service. At Norton Rose Fulbright, our strategy and our culture are closely entwined. We know that our expansion will mean little unless it is underpinned by truly global collaboration and we understand that pioneering work only takes place when our people have room to move and think beyond boundaries. As well as the relevant skills and experience, we're looking for people who are innovative, commercial and value the work that they do.\n\nSenior People & Culture Manager – Paris & Casablanca\n\nLocation: Paris\n\nTeam: People & Culture, EMEAPAC\n\nReports to: Head of People & Culture – Europe\n\nShape the future of People & Culture at a global law firm.\n\nAt Norton Rose Fulbright, we’re committed to creating an inclusive and high-performing workplace where our people thrive. We’re looking for a Senior People & Culture Manager to lead our People & Culture team for Paris and Casablanca and contribute to the broader EMEAPAC region. This is a fantastic opportunity for an experienced HR leader to work in a strategic and collaborative role within a truly international environment.\n\nAs the Senior People & Culture Manager, you will play a pivotal role in supporting our Partners and Business Services teams. You’ll lead a team of HR professionals, helping to deliver our People & Culture strategy while partnering closely with our regional and global Centres of Excellence (including Talent, Resourcing, Reward, Employee Relations, L&D and more).\n\nYou will report to the Head of People & Culture – Europe and work closely with the Chief Operating Officer for Paris & Casablanca to help shape the people agenda for the region.\n\nKey responsibilities include:\n\nActing as a strategic partner to business leaders, offering pragmatic, commercial and people-focused advice. Leading and developing a high-performing P&C team in Paris. Supporting change, engagement and performance initiatives across the region. Partnering with Centres of Excellence to deliver on key priorities (e.g. Talent, Reward, DE&I). Managing employee relations in line with firm-wide standards and local employment legislation. Driving talent, recruitment and retention strategies in collaboration with our Resourcing teams. Leading the annual performance review and compensation cycles. Promoting and advancing the Diversity, Equity & Inclusion agenda. Delivering key projects that align with the EMEAPAC People & Culture strategy. Implementing local HR policies, ensuring they reflect best practice and global alignment. \n\nWhat we’re looking for:\n\nSignificant HR leadership experience within a professional services or complex international environment. A confident business partner who is able to influence senior stakeholders and coach leaders. Proven ability to manage and develop HR teams, driving a high-performance culture. Strong knowledge of Paris employment law and HR and payroll practices. A collaborative and forward-thinking mindset with the ability to thrive in a matrixed, global organisation. Experience in leading Works CouncilsFluent in both French and English. \n\nWhat we offer:\n\nThe opportunity to work at a leading global law firm, with a strong people-first culture. A collaborative, international working environment with colleagues across Europe, the Middle East, Asia and beyond. The chance to shape and deliver impactful people strategies in a key market. Competitive salary and benefits package. \n\nReady to make an impact?\n\nIf you're an experienced HR professional looking to lead a dynamic team and help shape the people agenda in a global firm, we’d love to hear from you.\n\nApply now to join Norton Rose Fulbright and help us create a high-performance, high-support culture across Paris, Casablanca and beyond.\n\nDiversity, Equity and Inclusion\n\nTo attract the best people, we strive to create a diverse and inclusive environment where everyone can bring their whole selves to work, have a sense of belonging, and realize their full career potential.\n\nOur new enabled work model allows our people to have more flexibility in the way they choose to work from both the office and a remote location, while continuing to deliver the highest standards of service. We offer a range of family friendly and inclusive employment policies and provide access to programmes and services aimed at nurturing our people’s health and overall wellbeing. Find more about Diversity, Equity and Inclusion here.\n\nWe are proud to be an equal opportunities employer and encourage applications from individuals who can complement our existing teams. We strive to create an inclusive and accessible recruitment process for all candidates. If you require any tailored adjustments or accommodations, please let us know here.\n\n"}
