positions to senior level executives.Prospect, forecast, resource allocation, and planning of new business deals.Forecast sales activity and revenue achievement in CRM tool, while creating and maintaining satisfied customers.Achieve quarterly sales objectives and forecast sales activity accurately\nWhat You’ll Need:Years of Experience required: 5-13 years.Sales Professionals with experience in SAAS and AI5 to 10 years of experience in software solution sales.Contract Management or Procurement or Supply Chain domain knowledge – must be able to have credible business conversations with procurement, legal and finance executives.Demonstrable track record of consistent over achievement of quotas and revenue goalsExperience in managing complex sales-cycles and demonstrated ownership of territory and account management.Outstanding communication (written and oral), negotiation, presentation and solution selling skills to manage complex organizations.Demonstrated ability to work in an environment where growth and change is the only constant.Proficiency in Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, ExcelArabic Speaking is mandatoryA bachelor’s degree from a reputable institution\nCommitment to Diversity and Inclusion: We are an equal opportunity employer committed to diversity and inclusion. We do not discriminate based on race, color, gender, religion, national origin, ancestry, age, disability, medical condition, genetic information, military or veteran status, marital status, pregnancy, gender identity, sexual orientation, or any other protected characteristic. We provide reasonable accommodations for disabled employees and applicants as required by law. These principles apply to all aspects of employment, including recruitment, training, promotions, compensation, benefits, transfers, and social programs."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4406188516","title":"Country Manager","company":"Narwhal Labs","location":"Bristol","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://sa.linkedin.com/jobs/view/country-manager-at-narwhal-labs-4406188516?position=1&pageNum=0&refId=M42bZffTTx9NT225ur735Q%3D%3D&trackingId=WOTle7ZB1KaVn3PDycxDhQ%3D%3D","description":"📍 Saudi Arabia💼 Full-time💰 up to SAR 510,000 DOE\nAbout DeepBlue OS:DeepBlue OS is the Agentic AI Operating System built in Bristol. We run autonomous voice, SMS, email and WhatsApp communications for enterprise customers — deterministic, auditable, and built for regulated industries. Our Glass Box Architecture is what enterprise buys; our pricing is what SMBs need.In 2026 we're rolling internationally. Tier 1 markets are Ireland, Australia, UAE, and Saudi Arabia. The Country Manager is the first and only DeepBlue hire in-market — a solo operator who owns the full commercial picture, supported by the Global GTM Lead in Bristol.\nThe role:This is a builder role, not a manager role. The Country Manager owns one market's P&L from day one: partner acquisition, agency network, revenue, and market intelligence. There is no in-country team — full team setup follows only after market traction is proven at the 6-month gate. The Country Manager reports directly to the Global GTM Lead.The entry model is Deel EOR on Day 1. At month 6, if commercial gates are met, Narwhal incorporates a local entity and opens a Regus office. The Country Manager transitions from solo operator to team lead at that point.\nThe Narwhal expansion playbookIdentify — pick the one anchor partner whose distribution gives you bulk account volume (telco, MSP, trades platform).Prove — land them, white-label DeepBlue OS under their brand, process real volume.Scale — layer 5–10 local agencies on top of the anchor, open direct sign-ups, build vertical case studies.Move — hand the steady-state to a scaled team, take the learnings to the next vertical or country.\nWhat you ownRevenue for your market — from day one, with uncapped accelerators on channel revenueAnchor partner acquisition — the one deal that makes the whole market viable. You identify, qualify, pitch, and close it soloLocal agency network — recruited, enabled, and supported. 5–10 agencies operating by month 12Market intelligence — regulation, competition, partner moves — fed back to the Global GTM Lead weekly via Close CRM and SlackIn-country presence — trade events, industry associations, press, private C-suite dinners. You are DeepBlue in Saudi Arabia6-month gate readiness — you own all the conditions that determine whether Narwhal commits to a permanent entity and office\nWho we're looking for\nEssential8–12 years B2B channel or enterprise sales in your target marketDeep network at Director level or above inside one of: the dominant telco, a major trades/services platform, or a leading MSPProven track record closing 6- and 7-figure partnerships — not account managementSelf-directed solo operator — comfortable with a remote HQ and no in-country support teamCommercially sharp: unit economics, pricing models, building a business case for a technical product\nAdvantageousExperience in AI, SaaS, communications technology, or platform/marketplace businessesExperience with white-label or channel distribution modelsTrack record building a market from scratch, not inheriting an established territory\nMarket-specific requirementsSaudi Arabia — Native or fluent Arabic is essential — not optional. Deep KSA relationships at Director+ level inside STC, Mobily, or a top-10 Saudi services platform. Existing iqama/residency strongly preferred. Majlis rhythm and relationship-first long sales cycles is non-negotiable.\nWhat you getUncapped commission on partner and channel revenue, with accelerators on volume milestonesFull DeepBlue OS product training and Bristol onboarding in week oneQuarterly travel to Bristol HQ for SLT leadership offsites — flights and accommodation coveredClose CRM access, Cognism B2B data, and the full Bristol commercial infrastructure from day oneDirect line to the Global GTM Lead and CEO — no middle management\nWe don't run long recruitment processes. If you're right for this role, you'll speak to the Global GTM Lead within five working days. No recruiters - thank you."}
