{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=64533d985abaa4d2","title":"Maximo AI EAM Specialist","company":"MaxAccelerate","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"4 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=64533d985abaa4d2","description":"Job Title: Maximo AI EAM Specialist\n\nLocation: Remote / Hybrid (Global Projects)\nCompany: MaxAccelerate\nDepartment: AI & Intelligent Asset Management Practice\nType: Full-Time / Contract\n\nAbout the Role\n\nMaxAccelerate is one of the market leaders in MAS 9 / MAS 9.1 AI deployments, with over 50+ successful installations supporting customers and partners worldwide. As we grow our AI practice, we are looking for an experienced Maximo AI EAM Specialist to help organisations transform their operations using the latest MAS-native AI, WatsonX, and DataMax AI capabilities.\n\nThis is a rare opportunity to work at the forefront of the AI-native Maximo era. You will support clients in deploying, understanding and scaling their AI infrastructure, enabling them to move from reactive to predictive operations within months.\n\nIf you are passionate about Maximo, reliability, data, and the future of AI in asset management — this is the role for you.\n\nKey ResponsibilitiesAI & MAS 9.1 Implementation\nLead or support deployment of MAS 9.1 AI Services including:\nMaximo Assistant (natural language interface)\nWork Order Intelligence (problem code & classification recommendations)\nFMEA Builder\nEmbedded WatsonX LLM & ML capabilities\nReliability and maintenance AI workflows\n\nConfigure AI features to align with customer business rules, asset structures and operating models.\nIntelligent Reporting & Data Architecture\nWork with Cognos 12 and DataMax AI