{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c73f09b70f77db72","title":"Engineering Lead- Options","company":"Keyrock","location":"{\"city\":\"Abu Dhabi\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Abu Dhabi\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Abu Dhabi\",\"latitude\":24.46,\"longitude\":54.36,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"4 days ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c73f09b70f77db72","description":"Engineering Lead: Options\n\nAbout Keyrock\n\nSince our beginnings in 2017, we've grown to be a leading change-maker in the digital asset space, renowned for our partnerships and innovation.\n\nToday, we rock with over 200 team members around the world. Our diverse team hails from 42 nationalities, with backgrounds ranging from DeFi natives to PhDs. Predominantly remote, we have hubs in London, Madrid, Brussels, Singapore , New York and Paris, and host regular online and offline hangouts to keep the crew tight.\n\nWe are trading on more than 80 exchanges, and working with a wide array of asset issuers. As a well-established market maker, our distinctive expertise led us to expand rapidly. Today, our services span market making, options trading, high-frequency trading, OTC, and DeFi trading desks as well as asset and wealth management. Keyrock is looking to expand and establish itself as a full-service capital markets and asset & wealth management financial institution through both organic innovation and inorganic growth.\n\nBut we’re more than a service provider. We’re an initiator. We have been pioneers in adopting the Rust Development language for our algorithmic trading systems, and champions of its use in the industry. We upgrade Web3 ecosystems by injecting liquidity into promising DeFi, RWA, and NFT protocols. And we push the industry's progress with our research and governance initiatives.\n\nAt Keyrock, we're not just envisioning the future of digital assets. We're actively building it.\n\nMission statement\nWe are looking for a Head of Engineering / Engineering Lead with strong experience in systematic options trading to lead our Options Engineering team.\n\nIn this role, you will be responsible for leading the Options Engineering team, driving continuous improvement across the trading infrastructure, and supporting the evolution of our systematic options trading platform. This includes areas such as automated quoting, execution, risk controls, pricing workflows, and production reliability.\n\nWe are primarily looking for candidates based in European time zones or the US East Coast time zone.\n\nWe are looking for someone who can:\n\nLead and grow an Options Engineering team of around 7 engineers\n\nBring hands-on experience in systematic options trading, ideally including options market-making, automated quoting, execution, and risk management\n\nOwn and evolve an existing Rust-native systematic options trading platform\n\nProvide strong technical direction across trading infrastructure, system design, performance, reliability, and risk controls\n\nWork pragmatically through complex engineering and trading-system challenges\n\nPartner closely with trading, quant, product, risk, and infrastructure stakeholders\n\nBalance technical leadership with people leadership, delivery ownership, and operational discipline\n\nRequired Experience\n\n7+ years of experience in systematic trading, options market-making or low-latency trading systems\n\nStrong hands-on experience with Rust, C++, or C\n\nWillingness to become deeply proficient in Rust, if not already\n\nStrong understanding of algorithmic options trading, including automated quoting, execution, pricing, risk controls, and market data workflows\n\nExperience building or maintaining low-latency trading systems, ideally within options or derivatives markets\n\nExperience working with SQL databases in production environments, with PostgreSQL preferred\n\nFamiliarity with functional testing, component testing, and production-grade validation practices\n\nStrong understanding of distributed systems, service boundaries, and production reliability\n\nStrong knowledge of gRPC and experience working with Node.js-based services is preferred\n\nPrevious experience with crypto exchange connectivity and/or FPGA technologies is strongly preferred\n\nLeadership & Working Style\n\nStrong team player with the ability to lead, mentor, and guide engineers\n\nPragmatic approach to problem-solving, system design, and implementation\n\nAble to balance latency, reliability, safety, complexity, and delivery speed\n\nComfortable making technical decisions under uncertainty\n\nDemonstrates outside-the-box thinking while staying grounded in practical delivery\n\nCommunicates clearly and effectively, especially in unfamiliar or ambiguous contexts where clarity is critical\n\nAble to work closely with traders, quants, risk, product, and infrastructure stakeholders\n\nStrong ownership mindset, especially for production trading systems\n\nOur recruitment philosophy\n\nWe value self-awareness and powerful communication skills in our recruitment process. We seek fiercely passionate people who understand themselves and their career goals. We're after those with the right skills and a conscious choice to join our field. The perfect fit? A crypto enthusiast who’s driven, collaborative, acts with ownership and delivers solid, scalable outcomes.\n\nOur offer\n\nA competitive salary package\n\nAutonomy in your time management thanks to flexible working hours and the opportunity to work remotely\n\nThe freedom to create your own entrepreneurial experience by being part of a team of people in search of excellence\n\nAs an employer we are committed to building a positive and collaborative work environment. We welcome employees of all backgrounds, and hire, reward and promote entirely based on merit and performance.\n\nDue to the nature of our business and external requirements, we perform background checks on all potential employees, passing which is a prerequisite to join Keyrock.\n\nhttps://keyrock.com/careers/"}
