ect deck for regular distribution, ensuring it is designed to a high presentation standard.\nWork with Event and Department Coordinators to ensure this is accurate and continuously kept up to date to reflect the latest status and that it represents a \"source of truth\" of the overall project.\n\n Project Reporting:\nLead the creation and management of project reporting such as weekly client project reports, milestone and deliverables tracking and status reports.\nSupport in the creation of required post event reports and documents.\n\n Change Log:\nLead in the creation of Change Logs for select Project Fundamental Documents, including but not limited to: Site Plan Drawing(s), Staffing Grid, Schedule, RFP Tracker\nLogs should include a high level of detail, tracking dates, contact information, and change rationale.\n\n Document Control & Administration:\nSet up and maintain document control systems in accordance with project procedures.\nRegister all incoming and outgoing project documents in central repository (Box). Confirm all documents are properly indexed, categorized, and searchable.\nMaintain master document register and document status reports.\nManage document revisions, always ensuring correct version control and withdrawing superseded documents.\nOversee periodic and end of project reviews of department file systems to capture current relevant information and certify alignment with project filing systems and searchability for the client and/or other teams.\n\n Document Distribution:\nDistribute documents to internal teams, clients, and external stakeholders as per distribution lists and established cadence.\nAs documents are received, ensure they are distributed to relevant parties and teams.\nEnsure timely issuance of documents in accordance with project schedules and cadences.\n\n Project Support and Coordination:\nLiaise with Event Management and project departments to coordinate document workflows.\nInterface with suppliers and client to provide documentation as required.\nProvide guidance and training to project staff on document control procedures and systems and provide support in locating and retrieving documents.\nThis role is fluid in nature and may vary by project phase based on needs.\n\nPosition Requirements:\nBachelor's degree and 2 years minimum of event experience or similar.\nPast experience in the GCC area required, especially KSA, Dubai, Qatar, etc.\nHave excellent interpersonal & communication skills, both verbal & written.\nFluent English is a requirement for this position. Arabic or Urdu proficiency preferred but not required.\nPositive, “can do” attitude and approach to all tasks.\nExceptional attention to detail, maintaining high degree of accuracy and presentation\nComputer skills: Macintosh OS or Window platform using Microsoft Office, especially Outlook, Excel, and Powerpoint\nCreatively focused, with a keen eye for presentation / document layout.\nExperience using Monday.com, AirTable, Google docs, Smartsheet, or similar database and tracking software(or willing to learn).\nFlexibility to work irregular hours, including evenings, weekends, and holidays, based on event schedules.\nEnsure that all work conforms to pre-established specifications & standards.\nTake initiative, multi-task, and work positively in a fast-paced environment.\nWork with discretion, diplomacy, confidentiality, and tact in high-pressure settings.\nDemonstrate a sense of urgency & act responsively.\nWork independently as well as within a team environment.\nSupremely organized, detail-oriented, and thorough.\n\n TAIT is an equal opportunity employer fully committed to diversity and inclusion in the workplace. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, or status as a protected veteran or any other protected characteristic as outlined by international, national, state, or local laws."}
